abstract: Joe Biden bet his future as a Democratic presidential contender on South Carolina and its large pool of African-American voters,  and the backing of a leading black congressman vaulted him to victory there on Saturday, according to exit polls by Edison Research.
snippet: Joe Biden bet his future as a Democratic presidential contender on South Carolina and its large pool of African-American voters,  and the backing of a leading black congressman vaulted him to victory there on Saturday, according to exit polls by E...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Joe Biden bet his future as a Democratic presidential contender on South Carolina and its large pool of African-American voters, and the backing of a leading black congressman vaulted him to victory there on Saturday, according to exit polls by Edison Research.
headline_main: Key Black Lawmaker's Backing Factors Big in Biden's South Carolina Win: Poll
headline_print_headline: Key Black Lawmaker's Backing Factors Big in Biden's South Carolina Win: Poll

abstract: Former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg was not on the ballot in Saturday's Democratic presidential primary in South Carolina, but he was still on voters' minds - and not in a good way.
snippet: Former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg was not on the ballot in Saturday's Democratic presidential primary in South Carolina, but he was still on voters' minds - and not in a good way.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg was not on the ballot in Saturday's Democratic presidential primary in South Carolina, but he was still on voters' minds - and not in a good way.
headline_main: Bloomberg in South Carolina: Not on the Ballot and Not Liked-Poll
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg in South Carolina: Not on the Ballot and Not Liked-Poll

abstract: Vice President Joe Biden has for weeks looked to the black voters of South Carolina to hand a win to his flagging campaign. On Saturday, they delivered.
snippet: Vice President Joe Biden has for weeks looked to the black voters of South Carolina to hand a win to his flagging campaign. On Saturday, they delivered.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Vice President Joe Biden has for weeks looked to the black voters of South Carolina to hand a win to his flagging campaign. On Saturday, they delivered.
headline_main: AP VoteCast: Black Voters Carry Biden to His First Victory

abstract: Seeking to draw a direct contrast with President Trump, Mr. Bloomberg will deliver a three-minute prerecorded address on the coronavirus outbreak in an ad on network television Sunday night.
snippet: Seeking to draw a direct contrast with President Trump, Mr. Bloomberg will deliver a three-minute prerecorded address on the coronavirus outbreak in an ad on network television Sunday night.
lead_paragraph: Seeking to draw a direct contrast with President Trump and present himself as the best Democratic alternative, Michael R. Bloomberg will deliver a three-minute prerecorded address on the coronavirus outbreak in an ad on network television Sunday night, his campaign announced.

abstract: The activist hedge fund Elliott Management has taken a sizable stake in Twitter and called for changes at the social network.
snippet: The activist hedge fund Elliott Management has taken a sizable stake in Twitter and called for changes at the social network.
lead_paragraph: One of Wall Street’s most powerful activist hedge funds has taken a stake in Twitter and intends to shake up the social network — including by potentially calling for the replacement of its founder, Jack Dorsey, as chief executive, two people briefed on the matter said on Saturday.

abstract: A victory in Massachusetts would not just give Mr. Sanders a significant share of the state’s 91 delegates but also inflict a symbolic blow to his closest ideological rival.
snippet: A victory in Massachusetts would not just give Mr. Sanders a significant share of the state’s 91 delegates but also inflict a symbolic blow to his closest ideological rival.
lead_paragraph: SPRINGFIELD, Mass. — Bernie Sanders landed in Elizabeth Warren’s home state on Friday night, stood before thousands of screaming fans and asked them to help him win it.

abstract: As millions of Californians prepare to vote on Super Tuesday, the state’s affordability crisis is weighing heavily on their minds.
snippet: As millions of Californians prepare to vote on Super Tuesday, the state’s affordability crisis is weighing heavily on their minds.
lead_paragraph: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. — Mark Marquez, a retired Border Patrol agent, had hoped to keep his extended family intact in the same part of central California where his parents and grandparents had worked the watermelon fields.
